In this activity, you will be presented with questions that ask you to identify examples of plagiarism.

You will read five examples and it is your job to identify which actions show plagiarism.
Using parts of last year’s assignment in a new assignment without referencing it. Is this plagiarism?
Using parts of last year’s assignment in a new assignment without referencing it. Is this plagiarism?

Correct!

This is an example of plagiarism. Your assignments should be your own original work. It is okay to use ideas from previous assignments, but these should be referenced just as you would cite any other sources you use.
Using parts of last year’s assignment in a new assignment without referencing it. Is this plagiarism?

Wrong.

This is an example of plagiarism. Your assignments should be your own original work. It is okay to use ideas or text from previous assignments, but these should be referenced just as you would cite any other sources you use.
Copying and pasting information found on the internet into your work and handing it in as your own without referencing it.

Correct!

This is an example of plagiarism. If you submit an assignment the assumption is that you created everything in that assignment. It is okay to use outside resources to support your own ideas, but you should always cite any sources you took information from so you are not passing it off as your own ideas.
